## Context from audit

The audit flagged Anwil NDA as a pain point: > "Anwil NDA sat for weeks — contract first-pass review is slow."

This template is the chaser for those situations — where SRE has sent an NDA (or contract) and the counterparty's legal team has gone dark.

---

## Operator review checklist before send

- [ ] NDA version + send date verified (search Sent items)
- [ ] Weeks-in-review calculation correct
- [ ] Counterparty's legal contact email still active (not auto-bouncing or out-of-office)
- [ ] CC'd: counterparty's business contact (the person who owns the relationship, not just legal) — they apply pressure on their legal team
- [ ] SRE internal owner CC'd (typically Maaz himself + whoever's blocked by the NDA, e.g., Dharmesh if engineering work is held)
- [ ] Options A/B/C are appropriate for this counterparty — some prefer phone calls over multi-option emails
- [ ] No hostile tone — "this has been 6 weeks" is fine; "this is unacceptable delay" is not
- [ ] Length 80–120 words

**Approved by**: ______________ **Date**: __________

---

## Escalation rules

| Weeks in review | Tone | Action |
|---|---|---|
| 1–2 | Don't chase yet | Wait |
| 3–4 | Light check-in (Option D only — direct question) | Send |
| 5–8 | Multi-option chaser (this template) | Send |
| 9–12 | Escalate to business contact directly | Operator calls business contact; skip skill |
| 12+ | Consider whether the deal is dead | Operator decides retire-or-call-CEO |

