## Variant: contract (not NDA) — same shape, different stakes

For full contracts (MSA, project SOW, LTSA) the template structure is identical, but:

- Subject: `Contract review status: {{COUNTERPARTY}} - {{PROJECT_REFERENCE}}`
- Body: reference specific clauses if there's known back-and-forth on language
- CC: SRE legal (if external counsel involved) + project owner

---

## Variant: AIMS-relay NDA (Aramco etc.)

When the NDA path is SRE → AIMS → end-customer (typical for Aramco-class customers):

- **To**: AIMS contact (Bader, Shameem, etc.)
- Subject: `AIMS: NDA v{{N}} status with {{END_CUSTOMER}}`
- Body: ask AIMS for status on their side (AIMS legal review) + end-customer side
- The end-customer is NOT in To: or CC: — AIMS handles their side
